<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 6:54PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Clarke County
through 800 PM CDT...
At 654 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated
strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles west of
Grove Hill to 8 miles south of Whatley. Movement was south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Jackson, Grove Hill and Whatley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
